1 lawf ully occupied by such state or local government entity if the
2 display is made from a vehicle owned by or lawfully operated by such
3 person or if the display is being made by the person holding the
4 flag whether or not the display is made from a vehicle and if the
5 flag is being displayed in accordance with accepted standards for
6 the proper and respectful display of such flag and the flag has not
7 been altered or modified or defaced in any way.
8 B. The provisions of this section shall be applicable to a
9 motorcycle owned or lawfully operated by such person or any other
10 vehicle authorized pursuant to law to be operated on public roads or
11 highways.
12 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
